&lt;h1&gt;Theatre Practitioner - Ortho Scrub &lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic motivated individuals to join our friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;We are able to offer excellent development opportunities in Orthopaedics and Trauma theatres.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Nurses/Operating Department Practitioners who are keen to maintain and/or develop skills as scrub practitioners. Previous experience in a Perioperative or surgical nursing environment would be an advantage but full training and support will be given if necessary.  You will be supported by a mentor who will be able to offer support and assist with further development, and you will have the opportunity to rotate between scrub, recovery and anaesthetics if you so wish.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have excellent communication skills, be able to work well in a team and provide high quality patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lara David, Senior Sister at lara.david@nhs.net or 01225 826013 / Bleep 7627 or Milla Kivela, Senior Sister at milla.kivela@nhs.net or 01225 825703 / Bleep 7045.&lt;/p&gt;
